---
title: Mighty Mushroom Tortilla Melts with Caramelized Onion & an Apple Salad
description: Move over, quesadillas. These days, we’re all about tortilla melts! In all seriousness, though, our newest obsession is really just a spin on its south-of-the-border cousin. Our tortilla melts are similarly golden and crispy on the outside and packed with flavor (and cheese). Inside, there are savory sauteed mushrooms and onions, plus cheddar and Monterey Jack. It all gets drizzled with lemony crema and served alongside an apple-studded salad. Prepare to melt!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6239d54bf2907366e348025e-dcccfcf9.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/mighty-mushroom-tortilla-melts-6239d54bf2907366e348025e-1c0c8926.pdf
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 650 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 67 g
  sugar: 18 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 990 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mighty-mushroom-tortilla-melts-6239d54bf2907366e348025e
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
---

Wash and dry produce. Halve @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add
onion; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
softened, ~{7-9%minutes}.

> TIP: Lower heat and add a splash of water if onion begins to brown too
> quickly.

While onion cooks, halve @lemon{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}.
Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms
are pre-sliced!).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, ½ tsp
@fry seasoning{1%tablespoon} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and a squeeze of lemon
juice to taste; season with salt and pepper. (You'll use the rest of the
Fry Seasoning in the next step.)

In a #large bowl{}, toss apple and @mixed greens{2%ounce} with a drizzle of
@?olive oil{1%teaspoon} and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with
salt and pepper.

Once onion is softened, add mushrooms and a drizzle of oil to pan. Cook,
stirring occasionally, until mushrooms are tender and onion is caramelized,
~{2-4%minutes}. Season with salt, pepper, and remaining Fry Seasoning.

Add @mushroom stock concentrate{1} and 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings).
Cook, stirring, until liquid has mostly evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season
with salt and pepper.

> TIP: For an extra-rich filling, stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4).

Turn off heat; transfer filling to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface. Evenly sprinkle with
@cheddar cheese{½%cup}, then top with mushroom filling and
@Monterey Jack cheese{¼%cup}. Fold tortillas in half to create tortilla melts.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for filling over medium-high heat. Add
tortilla melts and cook until golden brown, ~{1-2%minutes}. Flip and cook
~{1%minute} more. (Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work
in batches.)

Transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate.

Transfer tortilla melts to a cutting board; cut into three wedges each.

Divide tortilla melts and salad between plates. Serve with crema on the side
for dipping.